column5: Went out Sunday morning around 6 on Cooks Bay, caught 5 decent pike from about 10-11. Great Day
looks like some heatlhy pike you got there!  Cheers!
looks like a good day  I have been finding fishing cooks bay a little slow this year
Hasn't been too bad, few pike here and there and quite a few bass. Have you been fishing further north? how's that been?
Some nice pike you caught there. I see the pike fishing is still thriving on cooks. Lots of bass you say? I assume Largies? Time to head there with the jig and pig! Thanks for sharing.
Nice outing man!  What did you catch them on? I've never had much luck for pike on cooks
Nice fish! How deep were you?
Thanks Guys, I've noticed the past 3-4 weeks that they are staying in the 15-20 foot mark. We caught all of them on an inline spinner.
Nice fish, you just saved some Perchies lives.
Sorry, catch and release always on pike, no perch are safe
Nice gators LefroyFisherman What was the weapon of choice for them beauties???  edit:  OK never mind my question.... inline spinners
